vulnerability.name: USN-3131-1
vulnerability.description: It was discovered that ImageMagick incorrectly handled certain malformed image files. If a user or automated system using ImageMagick were tricked into opening a specially crafted image, an attacker could exploit this to cause a denial of service or possibly execute code with the privileges of the user invoking the program.

statements.status_notes: Several security issues were fixed in ImageMagick.
